 Our block lies astride the{River Dee} 
 at the eastern end of{Royal Deeside.} 
 Two kilometresto the west lies the    
 rapidly expanding village of{Banchory}
 _ the largest settlement in{Deeside.} 
 Running on either side of the{River   
{Dee}lie the{North Deeside Road (A93)} 
 and the{South Deeside Road (A943).}   
 Between the river and each road lie   
 fertile terraces created by the action
 of the river. To the south of the     
 river the land rises quite sharply to 
 a height of about 300 feet (90        
 metres), while to the north, gentler, 
 heavily-wooded slopes also rise to a  
 height of about 300 feet.
